{
  "texts": [
    "An I-graded local system on ∂ is a local system V 0 → ∂ of finitedimensional vector spaces, together with a grading of each fibre V 0 d, with d ∈ ∂, by the set I d, in such a way that this grading is locally constant.",
    "This means that for any d ∈ ∂, there is a direct sum decomposition",
    "such that for any path γ from d to d ′ in ∂ (which naturally induces actions ρ γ:",
    "(Note that this definition works completely analogously if we replace the exponential local system I by any local system of sets on ∂.)",
    "For a fixed d ∈ ∂, let us set n i:= dim V 0 d (i) for i ∈ I d."
  ]
}